President Obama announced his intent to nominate Jon Leibowitz as Chairman of the Federal Trade Commission, Charlie Rose as General Counsel at the Department of Education, and Roy Keinitz as Under Secretary for Policy at the Department of Transportation. Leibowitz is currently the only Democratic Commissioner on the FTC and has a long career of public service. Keinitz is currently the Deputy Chief of Staff for Governor Rendell and has been a leader on transportation and environmental initiatives. Rose is a founding partner and corporate secretary of a law firm in Chicago and specializes in labor relations and education law.